  <a href="#1" id="1">
   Lucille Ball, the leggy showgirl, died early Wednesday, 04/26/1989, a week after undergoing emergency heart surgery.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   The co-creator and star of "I Love Lucy," was 77 and died at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center of a ruptured abdominal aorta.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   She had undergone surgery at Cedars-Sinai on 04/18/1989 to replace part of her aorta and aortic valve and had recovered from the 6 1/2-hour operation to a point where she was eating and even walking around her hospital room.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   The rupture occurred in a portion of the aorta, the main heart artery, far from where the operation was performed.
  </a>
